Event Summary: Pax holding service animal
Analyst Notes:
Messaged FA with FAM 3.9.8 and coached on regulation. 

• A guest may hold a small service animal (dog) on their lap provided the animal: 
_ Provides a task for the guest during the flight. 
_ Is no larger than an average two-year old child. 
_ Does not encroach on neighboring seat. 
_ A lap-held service animal may sit in the guest’s lap for all phases of flight including taxi, takeoff, and 
landing. If a carrier/kennel is used, it shall be stowed during taxi, takeoff, and landing
